# Breaking Bad

> _“Say my name.”_  
> **“You're Heisenberg.”**  
> **“You're goddamn right.”**

---

## 📺 Overview

**Breaking Bad** is an American neo-Western crime drama television series created by **Vince Gilligan**. It aired on **AMC** from 2008 to 2013.

---

## 🧪 Main Characters

- **Walter White** – Chemistry teacher turned meth kingpin
- **Jesse Pinkman** – Former student and partner in crime
- **Skyler White** – Walt’s wife
- **Hank Schrader** – DEA agent and Walt’s brother-in-law
- **Saul Goodman** – "Criminal" lawyer  
- **Gus Fring** – Drug kingpin and fast-food chain owner

---

## 🌟 Why I Love It

- Incredible storytelling and character development  
- Tension-filled scenes and unpredictable plot twists  
- Amazing performances, especially by **Bryan Cranston** and **Aaron Paul**

---

## 📌 Fun Facts

- The name "Breaking Bad" is a southern slang meaning "to turn to a life of crime"
- Bryan Cranston won **4 Emmy Awards** for his role
- It has a spin-off series: **Better Call Saul**

